@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(DOM-INIT-FILE-CLASS, 0018)
' @cycle(DOM-STATE-MIGRATION, 0018)
' @cycle(DOM-INIT-SEED-ONCE, 0022)
' @id(DOM-INIT-FILE-CLASS)
' @desc(DOM-INIT-FILE-CLASS, "Implemented as the routing in Project::init_with_conflict_handler plus the StateFile trait (crates/mdd-core/src/lib.rs). Regenerable files (docs, workflow SKILL.md, CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md managed blocks, SessionStart hook) go through write_text_if_missing(handler) / write_managed_block / write_session_hook and are safe to overwrite. AccumulatingState files (config.yml, trace.yml, approvals.yml) implement the StateFile trait and go through write_yaml_create_or_migrate, which never receives the conflict handler — so --force overwrites the Regenerable set but can never reach the AccumulatingState set. The split is the conceptual reason there are two distinct write paths.")
' @id(DOM-STATE-MIGRATION)
' @desc(DOM-STATE-MIGRATION, "Implemented by write_yaml_create_or_migrate + read_yaml_version + the StateFile trait (crates/mdd-core/src/lib.rs). schemaVersion = StateFile::schema_version() (read from each struct's Default — today 1 for MddConfig/Trace/Approvals); onDiskVersion = read_yaml_version() of the existing file (0 when absent/unparseable). migrate() fires only when onDiskVersion < schemaVersion: the file is deserialized into the current struct (fields added since fill from #[serde(default)]), set_schema_version stamps the current version, and it is re-serialized — every prior link/approval/config value survives, only newly-defaulted fields and the version change. onDiskVersion >= schemaVersion is skipped untouched (idempotent; never downgrade); an unparseable older file is also left untouched rather than clobbered. No per-version code.")
' @id(DOM-INIT-SEED-ONCE)
' @desc(DOM-INIT-SEED-ONCE, "Implemented as the third write path in Project::init_with_conflict_handler: write_text_create_if_missing (crates/mdd-core/src/lib.rs). A SeededOnce file is written from a template only when it does not yet exist, then never touched — it is not passed the conflict handler (so --force, whose always-Overwrite handler governs Regenerable files, can never reach it) and has no StateFile/version/migration path. It differs from Regenerable (write_text_if_missing(handler), overwritten by --force) and from AccumulatingState (write_yaml_create_or_migrate, versioned + forward-migrated). The instance is .mdd/ralph/PLAN.md (templates::ralph_plan()): the Ralph plan, which the model gap, a backlog, or another agent owns and rewrites, so init seeds it once and keeps its hands off. An existing PLAN.md is reported skipped, never overwritten.")
' Current-side domain for cycle 0018 (file-class split + state migration)
' and cycle 0022 (the SeededOnce class), mapped from the implemented engine.
title MDD init — file classes + state migration (current)

enum InitFileClass {
  Regenerable
  AccumulatingState
  SeededOnce
}

class StateMigration {
  + path : String
  + schemaVersion : u32
  + onDiskVersion : u32
  + migrate() : Outcome
}

enum Outcome {
  Created
  Migrated
  Skipped
}

StateMigration ..> InitFileClass : applies to AccumulatingState >
StateMigration ..> Outcome : yields >

note bottom of StateMigration
  migrate() (write_yaml_create_or_migrate):
    onDiskVersion < schemaVersion -> Migrated
      (parse into current struct, defaults fill
       new fields, bump version, write back)
    onDiskVersion = schemaVersion -> Skipped (untouched)
    onDiskVersion > schemaVersion -> Skipped (no downgrade)
  Preserves all prior content; no per-version code.
end note

note bottom of InitFileClass
  Regenerable: docs, skills (incl. mdd-ralph),
  CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md blocks, SessionStart hook,
  .mdd/ralph/PROMPT.md -> --force overwrites.
  AccumulatingState (StateFile trait): config / trace /
  approvals -> never overwritten; created or migrated.
  SeededOnce (DOM-INIT-SEED-ONCE): .mdd/ralph/PLAN.md ->
  write_text_create_if_missing; never overwritten
  (even by --force) and never migrated.
end note
@enduml
